    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I am still unsure (even if that's we do today) that ALWAYS scrolling to top is better. It really depends on the website height and the widgets we have.\n\nSlider should not automatically scroll to top.\n\nrefinementList should not automatically scroll to top because I may want to select \"red\" and \"blue\" checkboxes. While the behavior will make me angry because it did something I did not want.\n\nSo only for the pagination should be ok for now.\n\nWe still can have a proposal of an `.on('refine')` event allowing users to do anything they want.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-09-09T08:26:26Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/73#issuecomment-138822830",
