  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure this is a safe default. I don't always want to scroll to top when paginating. Maybe the page header is tall, and I've already correctly scrolled my page to only have the hits in my view port. Scrolling to top will break that.\n\nI'd be more in favor of a more generic `.on('refine')` to let users do what they want\n",
